{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885096536,"sessionID":"ses_285003684ffefPGdIjY7Or0ClI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0009c90015NWQycjPefrAli","messageID":"msg_d7affe5f40017F5gTds0yWcIr7","sessionID":"ses_285003684ffefPGdIjY7Or0ClI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-18494c6fe97c4356be2ae0e9474c2f6d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Define Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                         RBAC Architecture                                    │\n24: │                     AgentCube Components                                     │\n25: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n26: │                                                                              │\n27: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n28: │  │                    Router RBAC (Namespace-scoped)                     │   │\n29: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤   │\n30: │  │                                                                       │   │\n31: │  │   ┌─────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐                      │   │\n32: │  │   │ ServiceAccount  │──────│ RoleBinding     │                      │   │\n33: │  │   │ (namespace)     │      │ (namespace)     │                      │   │\n34: │  │   └─────────────────┘      └─────────────────┘                      │   │\n35: │  │                                  │                                   │   │\n36: │  │                                  ▼                                   │   │\n37: │  │                          ┌─────────────────┐                        │   │\n38: │  │                          │ Role            │                        │   │\n39: │  │                          │ (secrets only)  │                        │   │\n40: │  │                          └─────────────────┘                        │   │\n41: │  │                                                                       │   │\n42: │  │   Scope: {{ .Release.Namespace }}                                     │   │\n43: │  │   Permissions: secrets (get/list/watch/create/update/patch/delete)   │   │\n44: │  │   Conditional: router.rbac.create=true                                │   │\n45: │  │                                                                       │   │\n46: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n47: │                                                                              │\n48: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n49: │  │              WorkloadManager RBAC (Cluster-wide)                      │   │\n50: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤   │\n51: │  │                                                                       │   │\n52: │  │   ┌─────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐                  │   │\n53: │  │   │ ServiceAccount  │──────│ ClusterRoleBinding  │                  │   │\n54: │  │   │ (namespace)     │      │ (cluster-wide)      │                  │   │\n55: │  │   └─────────────────┘      └─────────────────────┘                  │   │\n56: │  │                                  │                                   │   │\n57: │  │                                  ▼                                   │   │\n58: │  │                          ┌─────────────────────┐                    │   │\n59: │  │                          │ ClusterRole         │                    │   │\n60: │  │                          │ (CRDs, Pods,        │                    │   │\n61: │  │                          │  Secrets,           │                    │   │\n62: │  │                          │  TokenReviews)      │                    │   │\n63: │  │                          └─────────────────────┘                    │   │\n64: │  │                                                                       │   │\n65: │  │   Scope: Cluster-wide                                                 │   │\n66: │  │   Permissions:                                                        │   │\n67: │  │     - agents.x-k8s.io: sandboxes                                      │   │\n68: │  │     - extensions.agents.x-k8s.io: sandboxclaims, templates, warmpools │   │\n69: │  │     - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh: codeinterpreters, agentruntimes   │   │\n70: │  │     - core: pods, secrets                                             │   │\n71: │  │     - authentication.k8s.io: tokenreviews                             │   │\n72: │  │                                                                       │   │\n73: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n74: │                                                                              │\n75: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### RBAC Permission Model\n79: \n80: ```\n81: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │                      Permission Flow Diagram                                  │\n83: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n84: │                                                                              │\n85: │   User/External ──────▶ Router ──────▶ Secrets (namespace-scoped)           │\n86: │         │                  │                                                │\n87: │         │                  │         ┌──────────────────────────────────┐   │\n88: │         │                  │         │ Role: secrets                    │   │\n89: │         │                  │         │ Verbs: get,list,watch,           │   │\n90: │         │                  │         │        create,update,patch,delete│   │\n91: │         │                  │         └──────────────────────────────────┘   │\n92: │         │                  │                                                │\n93: │         ▼                  ▼                                                │\n94: │                                                                              │\n95: │   Router ──────▶ WorkloadManager ──────▶ Kubernetes API                    │\n96: │         │                  │                                                │\n97: │         │                  │         ┌──────────────────────────────────┐   │\n98: │         │                  │         │ ClusterRole:                     │   │\n99: │         │                  │         │ - Sandboxes (full CRUD)          │   │\n100: │         │                  │         │ - CodeInterpreters (full CRUD)   │   │\n101: │         │                  │         │ - AgentRuntimes (read + status)  │   │\n102: │         │                  │         │ - Pods (read-only)               │   │\n103: │         │                  │         │ - Secrets (full CRUD)            │   │\n104: │         │                  │         │ - TokenReviews (create)          │   │\n105: │         │                  │         └──────────────────────────────────┘   │\n106: │         │                  │                                                │\n107: │         │                  ▼                                                │\n108: │         │         ┌─────────────────┐                                      │\n109: │         │         │ Sandbox CRDs    │──▶ Agent Sandbox Controller         │\n110: │         │         └─────────────────┘                                      │\n111: │         │         ┌─────────────────┐                                      │\n112: │         │         │ AgentCube CRDs  │──▶ WorkloadManager Reconciler        │\n113: │         │         └─────────────────┘                                      │\n114: │         │         ┌─────────────────┐                                      │\n115: │         │         │ Pods/Secrets    │──▶ Kubernetes Core API               │\n116: │         │         └─────────────────┘                                      │\n117: │         │                                                                  │\n118: │                                                                              │\n119: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n120: ```\n121: \n122: ### Component Relationships\n123: \n124: | Component | Scope | Resources | Purpose |\n125: |-----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n126: | Router ServiceAccount | Namespace | Pod identity | JWT signing key, identity secret access |\n127: | Router Role | Namespace | secrets | Manage session secrets |\n128: | Router RoleBinding | Namespace | SA → Role | Bind Router SA to Role |\n129: | WorkloadManager ServiceAccount | Namespace | Pod identity | CRD operations, sandbox lifecycle |\n130: | WorkloadManager ClusterRole | Cluster | CRDs, pods, secrets, tokenreviews | Full sandbox/interpreter management |\n131: | WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding | Cluster | SA → ClusterRole | Bind WM SA to ClusterRole |\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ## Data Structures\n136: \n137: ### Router RBAC Schema\n138: \n139: #### ServiceAccount\n140: \n141: ```yaml\n142: apiVersion: v1\n143: kind: ServiceAccount\n144: metadata:\n145:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n146:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n147:   labels:\n148:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n149:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n150:     app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n151:     app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### Role\n155: \n156: ```yaml\n157: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n158: kind: Role\n159: metadata:\n160:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n161:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n162:   labels:\n163:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n164:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n165: rules:\n166:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n167:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n168:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### RoleBinding\n172: \n173: ```yaml\n174: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n175: kind: RoleBinding\n176: metadata:\n177:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n178:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n179:   labels:\n180:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n181:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n182: roleRef:\n183:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n184:   kind: Role\n185:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n186: subjects:\n187:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n188:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n189:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### WorkloadManager RBAC Schema\n193: \n194: #### ServiceAccount\n195: \n196: ```yaml\n197: apiVersion: v1\n198: kind: ServiceAccount\n199: metadata:\n200:   name: workloadmanager\n201:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n202:   labels:\n203:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n204:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n205: ```\n206: \n207: #### ClusterRole\n208: \n209: ```yaml\n210: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n211: kind: ClusterRole\n212: metadata:\n213:   name: workloadmanager\n214:   labels:\n215:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n216: rules:\n217:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n218:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n219:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n220:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n221:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n222:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n223:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n224:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n225:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n226:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n227:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n228:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n229:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n230:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n231:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n232:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n233:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n234:     verbs: [\"update\"]\n235:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n236:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n237:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n238:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n239:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n240:     verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n241:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n242:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n243:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n244:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n245:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n246:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n247:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n248:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n249:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n250: ```\n251: \n252: #### ClusterRoleBinding\n253: \n254: ```yaml\n255: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n256: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n257: metadata:\n258:   name: workloadmanager\n259:   labels:\n260:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n261: roleRef:\n262:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n263:   kind: ClusterRole\n264:   name: workloadmanager\n265: subjects:\n266:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n267:     name: workloadmanager\n268:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ### RBAC Permission Matrix\n272: \n273: #### Router Role (Namespace-scoped)\n274: \n275: | apiGroups | Resources | Verbs | Reason |\n276: |-----------|-----------|-------|--------|\n277: | `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | JWT signing keys, identity secrets |\n278: \n279: #### WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n280: \n281: | apiGroups | Resources | Verbs | Reason |\n282: |-----------|-----------|-------|--------|\n283: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxes | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Sandbox lifecycle management |\n284: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Extension CRD management |\n285: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | WarmPool status updates |\n286: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | CodeInterpreter lifecycle |\n287: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource updates |\n288: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management |\n289: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | AgentRuntime read access |\n290: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Runtime status updates |\n291: | `\"\"` (core) | pods | get, list, watch | Pod monitoring (no create/delete) |\n292: | `\"\"` (core) | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete | Sandbox secrets management |\n293: | `authentication.k8s.io` | tokenreviews | create | Token authentication |\n294: \n295: ### Values.yaml RBAC Configuration\n296: \n297: ```yaml\n298: router:\n299:   serviceAccountName: \"\"       # Required when router.rbac.create=true\n300:   rbac:\n301:     create: false              # Default: disabled, enable for self-contained RBAC\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ## API Contracts\n307: \n308: ### Router RBAC Template Contract\n309: \n310: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n311: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n312: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | No | Default `false`. Enable to create Router RBAC |\n313: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | Conditional | Required when `rbac.create=true` |\n314: \n315: ### Validation Contract\n316: \n317: ```\n318: IF router.rbac.create == true AND router.serviceAccountName == \"\"\n319: THEN fail(\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\")\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Router Deployment Integration\n323: \n324: ```yaml\n325: spec:\n326:   template:\n327:     spec:\n328:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n329:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n330:       {{- end }}\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### RBAC Rendering Contract\n334: \n335: | Condition | Rendered Resources |\n336: |-----------|--------------------|\n337: | `router.rbac.create=true` | ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding |\n338: | `router.rbac.create=false` | None (user provides external RBAC) |\n339: | WorkloadManager (always) | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## Error Handling\n344: \n345: ### Template Validation Errors\n346: \n347: | Error | Condition | Resolution |\n348: |-------|-----------|------------|\n349: | `router.serviceAccountName must be set` | `rbac.create=true` without SA name | Set `router.serviceAccountName` in values.yaml |\n350: | `Helm lint error` | Invalid YAML syntax | Fix template syntax |\n351: | `Render error` | Undefined helper template | Verify `agentcube.labels` in `_helpers.tpl` |\n352: | `Missing namespace` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` undefined | Ensure Helm 3+ with namespace context |\n353: \n354: ### Template Validation Pattern\n355: \n356: ```yaml\n357: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n358: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n359: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n360: {{- end }}\n361: # RBAC resources...\n362: {{- end }}\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ### Kubernetes RBAC Errors\n366: \n367: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n368: |-------|-------|------------|\n369: | `Forbidden` | Missing RBAC permission | Verify Role/ClusterRole rules |\n370: | `ServiceAccount not found` | SA not created | Check RBAC template rendered |\n371: | `RoleBinding references non-existent Role` | Role not created | Verify Role template |\n372: | `Cannot create cluster resource` | Namespace Role for cluster resource | Use ClusterRole for cluster-scoped resources |\n373: \n374: ### Permission Denial Patterns\n375: \n376: | Scenario | Expected Behavior | Error Message |\n377: |----------|-------------------|---------------|\n378: | Router access secret in other namespace | Forbidden | `secrets \"xxx\" is forbidden: User cannot get resource \"secrets\" in API group \"\" in namespace \"other-ns\"` |\n379: | Router create Pod | Forbidden | `pods is forbidden: User cannot create resource \"pods\"` |\n380: | WorkloadManager create Pod directly | Forbidden | `pods is forbidden: User cannot create resource \"pods\"` (only read) |\n381: | WorkloadManager delete AgentRuntime | Forbidden | `agentruntimes is forbidden: User cannot delete` (only read) |\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Testing Strategy\n386: \n387: ### Test Categories\n388: \n389: | Category | Scope | Tools | Purpose |\n390: |----------|-------|-------|---------|\n391: | Helm lint | Chart syntax | `helm lint` | Validate template syntax |\n392: | Template render | YAML output | `helm template` | Verify RBAC resources rendered |\n393: | Validation guard | Conditional logic | `helm template --set` | Test fail conditions |\n394: | kubectl dry-run | API schema | `kubectl apply --dry-run` | Validate Kubernetes schema |\n395: | E2E deployment | Full stack | `helm install` | Verify RBAC grants work |\n396: \n397: ### Helm Lint Test\n398: \n399: ```bash\n400: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n401: # Expected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n402: ```\n403: \n404: ### Template Render Tests\n405: \n406: #### Test: Router RBAC enabled\n407: \n408: ```bash\n409: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n410:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n411:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n412:   --namespace agentcube-test | grep -A20 \"kind: ServiceAccount\"\n413: \n414: # Expected: Router ServiceAccount with name \"agentcube-router\"\n415: # Expected: Router Role with secrets permissions\n416: # Expected: Router RoleBinding binding SA to Role\n417: ```\n418: \n419: #### Test: Router RBAC disabled\n420: \n421: ```bash\n422: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n423:   --set router.rbac.create=false \\\n424:   --namespace agentcube-test | grep \"kind: Role\"\n425: \n426: # Expected: No Router Role/RoleBinding/SA (only WorkloadManager RBAC)\n427: ```\n428: \n429: #### Test: Validation guard\n430: \n431: ```bash\n432: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n433:   --set router.rbac.create=true\n434: \n435: # Expected: Error \"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"\n436: ```\n437: \n438: ### kubectl Dry-run Tests\n439: \n440: ```bash\n441: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n442:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n443:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n444:   --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" \\\n445:   > /tmp/rendered.yaml\n446: \n447: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml\n448: # Expected: No validation errors\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Permission Matrix Tests\n452: \n453: | Test Case | Command | Expected |\n454: |-----------|---------|----------|\n455: | Router can read secrets | `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `yes` |\n456: | Router cannot read pods | `kubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `no` |\n457: | Router cannot access other ns | `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:router-sa` | `no` |\n458: | WorkloadManager can create sandboxes | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n459: | WorkloadManager can create codeinterpreters | `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n460: | WorkloadManager cannot create pods | `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `no` |\n461: | WorkloadManager can create tokenreviews | `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:ns:workloadmanager` | `yes` |\n462: \n463: ### Security Audit Tests\n464: \n465: ```bash\n466: # No wildcard permissions\n467: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n468:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n469:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n470:   | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]'\n471: \n472: # Expected: No matches (wildcards not allowed)\n473: \n474: # No TokenReview for Router\n475: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n476:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n477:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n478:   | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep tokenreviews\n479: \n480: # Expected: No matches (Router has no TokenReview permission)\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### E2E Test Cases\n484: \n485: | Test | Setup | Verification |\n486: |------|-------|--------------|\n487: | Router secret lifecycle | Deploy with RBAC enabled | Router creates/reads/updates/deletes secrets in namespace |\n488: | Router namespace isolation | Deploy in ns-A, create secret in ns-B | Router access to ns-B secret fails |\n489: | WorkloadManager sandbox create | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager creates Sandbox CRD |\n490: | WorkloadManager codeinterpreter lifecycle | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager manages CodeInterpreter CRD |\n491: | WorkloadManager pod read | Deploy with RBAC | WorkloadManager lists pods, cannot create/delete |\n492: \n493: ### Test Commands Summary\n494: \n495: ```bash\n496: # 1. Helm lint\n497: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n498: \n499: # 2. Render with RBAC enabled\n500: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n501:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n502:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n503:   --namespace agentcube\n504: \n505: # 3. Validation guard test\n506: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n507:   --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"\n508: \n509: # 4. Dry-run validation\n510: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n511:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n512:   --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router \\\n513:   | kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f -\n514: \n515: # 5. Permission audit\n516: kubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager\n517: kubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube\n518: ```\n519: \n520: ---\n521: \n522: ## File Structure\n523: \n524: | Path | Role |\n525: |------|------|\n526: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding (conditional) |\n527: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n528: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template `agentcube.labels` |\n529: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | `router.rbac.create`, `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n530: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment (uses ServiceAccount) |\n531: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment (uses ServiceAccount) |\n532: \n533: ---\n534: \n535: ## Dependencies\n536: \n537: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n538: |---------|---------|---------|\n539: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n540: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals, validation guards (`fail` function) |\n541: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool |\n542: | `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n543: \n544: ---\n545: \n546: ## Implementation Notes\n547: \n548: ### RBAC Scope Design\n549: \n550: | Component | Scope | Reason |\n551: |-----------|-------|--------|\n552: | Router | Namespace-scoped Role | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT keys, identity) |\n553: | WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped ClusterRole | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; cross-namespace sandbox management |\n554: \n555: ### Least Privilege Principle\n556: \n557: | Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n558: |----------|-------|--------|\n559: | pods | get, list, watch | Read-only for monitoring; WorkloadManager creates via Sandbox CRD |\n560: | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; no direct lifecycle management |\n561: | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only, no delete |\n562: | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern |\n563: | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only |\n564: | tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete |\n565: \n566: ### Conditional RBAC Pattern\n567: \n568: Router RBAC is optional to support:\n569: 1. **Self-contained deployment**: `rbac.create=true` creates RBAC automatically\n570: 2. **External RBAC management**: `rbac.create=false` with pre-existing SA for IAM integration\n571: \n572: ### Namespace Isolation\n573: \n574: Router Role is explicitly namespace-scoped:\n575: - Role metadata includes `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n576: - RoleBinding binds SA within same namespace\n577: - No ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n578: - Router cannot access secrets in other namespaces\n579: \n580: ### ServiceAccount Naming\n581: \n582: | Component | Name Source | Default |\n583: |-----------|-------------|---------|\n584: | Router | `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` | Empty (user must set) |\n585: | WorkloadManager | Fixed: `workloadmanager` | Always `workloadmanager` |\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## References\n590: \n591: - Spec: `changes/AR-031/spec.md`\n592: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n593: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n594: - Tasks: `changes/AR-031/tasks.md`\n595: - Router RBAC Template: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n596: - WorkloadManager RBAC Template: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n597: - Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md`\n598: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n599: - Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n\n(End of file - total 599 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/design.md","time":{"start":1775885096489,"end":1775885096533}}}}
