{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885263016,"sessionID":"ses_285003684ffefPGdIjY7Or0ClI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b02a011001Aw2z0LcFxApJqJ","messageID":"msg_d7b00a36d001YZDqA7619enrMg","sessionID":"ses_285003684ffefPGdIjY7Or0ClI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-b1b4cfb25b9f46d89b87feebe38f7c49","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","content":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create Router ServiceAccount template with conditional rendering\n  - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount when `router.rbac.create=true`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: agentcube-router\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: Implement Router ServiceAccount validation guard\n  - Purpose: Fail if `router.rbac.create=true` but `router.serviceAccountName` not set\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3**: Define Router Role with namespace-scoped secrets permissions\n  - Purpose: Create Role with `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` for secrets\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"secrets\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.4**: Create Router RoleBinding to bind ServiceAccount to Role\n  - Purpose: Establish SA → Role binding within namespace\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: RoleBinding\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.5**: Implement Router Role namespace isolation\n  - Purpose: Ensure Role and RoleBinding are namespace-scoped (not cluster-wide)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n\n### Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC (ST-2)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1**: Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount template\n  - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager (cluster-scoped identity)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: workloadmanager\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n  - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxes` (full CRUD)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxes\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n  - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` and status subresource\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxclaims\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.4**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh CRDs\n  - Purpose: Grant full CRUD for `codeinterpreters` + status/finalizers, read-only for `agentruntimes` + status updates\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A20 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"codeinterpreters\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.5**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for core Kubernetes resources\n  - Purpose: Grant read-only for `pods`, full CRUD for `secrets`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A25 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"pods\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.6**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for TokenReview\n  - Purpose: Grant `create` permission for `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A30 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"tokenreviews\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.7**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n  - Purpose: Bind ClusterRole to ServiceAccount (cluster-wide binding)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A10 \"kind: ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n\n### Phase 3: Deployment Integration (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Integrate Router ServiceAccount into Router Deployment\n  - Purpose: Set `serviceAccountName` in Router Deployment spec when `router.serviceAccountName` is provided\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Integrate WorkloadManager ServiceAccount into WorkloadManager Deployment\n  - Purpose: Set fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager` in WorkloadManager Deployment\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"name: workloadmanager\" | grep \"serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\"`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3**: Update values.yaml with router.rbac.create configuration\n  - Purpose: Add `router.rbac.create: false` default and `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n  - Verification: `grep \"rbac:\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml && grep \"create: false\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n\n### Phase 4: Permission Validation (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Verify Router Role has no wildcard permissions\n  - Purpose: Ensure no `*` in resources or verbs (least-privilege compliance)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Verify Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n  - Purpose: Router should only have secrets access (no authentication API)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"tokenreviews\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no Pod create/delete permissions\n  - Purpose: WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no AgentRuntime delete permission\n  - Purpose: WorkloadManager only reads AgentRuntimes, cannot delete\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"delete\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T4.5**: Verify all ClusterRole rules use correct API groups\n  - Purpose: Validate API groups: `agents.x-k8s.io`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `authentication.k8s.io`, core `\"\"`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"apiGroups\"`\n\n### Phase 5: Helm Chart Validation Tests (ST-5)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1**: Run Helm lint on chart with RBAC enabled\n  - Purpose: Validate chart syntax with Router RBAC enabled\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n  - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2**: Test Router RBAC disabled scenario\n  - Purpose: Verify no Router RBAC resources rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: Role\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3**: Test Router RBAC validation guard failure\n  - Purpose: Verify template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without serviceAccountName\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4**: Test Router RBAC rendering with custom namespace\n  - Purpose: Verify RBAC resources use correct namespace from Helm release\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n\n- [ ] **T5.5**: Test WorkloadManager RBAC always rendered\n  - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC renders regardless of Router RBAC setting\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\"`\n\n### Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation Tests (ST-6)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1**: Validate Router RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n  - Purpose: Verify Router RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/router-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/router-rbac.yaml | grep \"serviceaccount\"`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2**: Validate WorkloadManager RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n  - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml | grep \"clusterrole\"`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3**: Validate complete chart with kubectl dry-run\n  - Purpose: Verify entire rendered chart is valid for Kubernetes API\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml`\n\n### Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests (ST-7)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1**: Test Router ServiceAccount can access secrets in own namespace\n  - Purpose: Verify `kubectl auth can-i` returns `yes` for Router SA secrets access\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: yes)\n\n- [ ] **T7.2**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot access secrets in other namespace\n  - Purpose: Verify namespace isolation - Router SA forbidden in other namespaces\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router` (expected: no)\n\n- [ ] **T7.3**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot create pods\n  - Purpose: Verify Router has no pod creation permission\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: no)\n\n- [ ] **T7.4**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create sandboxes\n  - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has sandbox creation permission\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n\n- [ ] **T7.5**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create codeinterpreters\n  - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has CodeInterpreter CRD permissions\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n\n- [ ] **T7.6**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot create pods directly\n  - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager cannot create Pods (only via Sandbox CRD)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n\n- [ ] **T7.7**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create TokenReviews\n  - Purpose: Verify TokenReview create permission for authentication\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n\n- [ ] **T7.8**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot delete AgentRuntimes\n  - Purpose: Verify AgentRuntime is read-only for WorkloadManager\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n  - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i delete agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n\n### Phase 8: Security Audit Tests (ST-8)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1**: Verify no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n  - Purpose: Router should only have namespace-scoped Role (not cluster-wide)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2**: Verify Router Role metadata includes namespace\n  - Purpose: Confirm Role is namespace-scoped (not cluster-scoped)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep -A3 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"namespace\"`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for pods\n  - Purpose: Pods should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/update/delete)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|update|patch|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T8.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for agentruntimes\n  - Purpose: AgentRuntimes should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/delete)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"verbs\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **T8.5**: Verify no wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n  - Purpose: Security audit - wildcards violate least-privilege principle\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/`\n  - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nPhase 1 (Router RBAC Foundation) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nT1.1 (SA) ──┬── T1.2 (validation guard)\n            ├── T1.3 (Role)\n            ├── T1.4 (RoleBinding)\n            └── T1.5 (namespace isolation)\n\nPhase 2 (WorkloadManager RBAC) ───────────────────────────────────────────────\nT2.1 (SA) ──┬── T2.2 (agents.x-k8s.io)\n            ├── T2.3 (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io)\n            ├── T2.4 (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)\n            ├── T2.5 (core resources)\n            ├── T2.6 (TokenReview)\n            └── T2.7 (ClusterRoleBinding)\n\nPhase 3 (Deployment Integration) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nT1.1-T1.5 ──┬── T3.1 (Router Deployment)\nT2.1-T2.7 ──┬── T3.2 (WorkloadManager Deployment)\n            └── T3.3 (values.yaml)\n\nPhase 4 (Permission Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────────\nT1.1-T3.3 ──┬── T4.1-T4.5 (permission matrix validation)\n\nPhase 5 (Helm Validation) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nT1.1-T4.5 ──┬── T5.1-T5.5 (Helm template tests)\n\nPhase 6 (Kubernetes API Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────\nT5.1-T5.5 ──┬── T6.1-T6.3 (kubectl dry-run tests)\n\nPhase 7 (Permission Matrix Tests) ────────────────────────────────────────────\nT6.1-T6.3 ──┬── T7.1-T7.8 (kubectl auth can-i tests) [requires cluster]\n\nPhase 8 (Security Audit) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nT1.1-T7.8 ──┬── T8.1-T8.5 (security audit checks)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n| Task Phase | Verification Command |\n|------------|----------------------|\n| Phase 1 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: ServiceAccount\" \\| grep \"name: test-sa\"` |\n| Phase 2 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep \"sandboxes\"` |\n| Phase 3 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"` |\n| Phase 4 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"` |\n| Phase 5 | `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa` |\n| Phase 6 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml` |\n| Phase 7 | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (requires cluster deployment) |\n| Phase 8 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep -v workloadmanager || echo \"OK\"` |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Router ServiceAccount rendered when `router.rbac.create=true`\n- [ ] Router Role has namespace-scoped secrets permissions (get/list/watch/create/update/patch/delete)\n- [ ] Router RoleBinding binds Router SA to Router Role within namespace\n- [ ] Router RBAC validation guard: fail if `router.rbac.create=true` without `router.serviceAccountName`\n- [ ] Router RBAC not rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n- [ ] Router RBAC has no cluster-scoped resources (no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding)\n- [ ] Router RBAC uses correct namespace from `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ServiceAccount always rendered\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes (full CRUD)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io (sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools + status)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters (full CRUD + status/finalizers)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes (read-only + status updates)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core pods (read-only: get/list/watch)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core secrets (full CRUD)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permission for authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews (create only)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding binds WM SA to WM ClusterRole\n- [ ] Router Deployment uses `router.serviceAccountName` when provided\n- [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment uses fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager`\n- [ ] values.yaml includes `router.rbac.create: false` default\n- [ ] values.yaml includes `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n- [ ] Helm lint passes with 0 errors\n- [ ] Rendered YAML validates with kubectl dry-run\n- [ ] Router SA can access secrets in own namespace (kubectl auth can-i)\n- [ ] Router SA cannot access secrets in other namespaces (namespace isolation)\n- [ ] Router SA cannot create pods (least-privilege)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create sandboxes CRDs\n- [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create codeinterpreter CRDs\n- [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot create pods directly (only via Sandbox)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot delete agentruntimes (read-only)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create TokenReviews\n- [ ] No wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n- [ ] Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n- [ ] All RBAC rules use correct API groups\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines | Description |\n|------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Create | 49 | Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding - conditional rendering) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Create | 131 | WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Modify | 81 | Add serviceAccountName field integration |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Modify | - | Add serviceAccountName: workloadmanager (if missing) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modify | 57 | Add router.rbac.create and router.serviceAccountName defaults |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Router RBAC Conditional Rendering Pattern\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n{{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n{{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n{{- end }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\nsubjects:\n  - kind: ServiceAccount\n    name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n    namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### WorkloadManager ClusterRole Permission Matrix\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nrules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n    verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"pods\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n    resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n    verbs: [\"create\"]\n  \n  - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n    resources: [\"secrets\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n### RBAC Scope Design Rationale\n\n| Component | Scope | Reason |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| Router | Namespace-scoped (Role/RoleBinding) | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT signing keys, identity secrets). No cluster-wide access needed. |\n| WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped (ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding) | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; WorkloadManager manages sandboxes across namespaces. Cross-namespace sandbox lifecycle management requires cluster-wide permissions. |\n\n### Least Privilege Principles\n\n| Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n|----------|-------|--------|\n| pods | get, list, watch | Read-only monitoring; WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly |\n| agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; WorkloadManager references AgentRuntimes but does not manage lifecycle |\n| agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only; no delete permission |\n| sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern; separate from main resource CRUD |\n| codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only; limited to finalizer operations |\n| tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete (ephemeral operation) |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Timeline\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n|-------|-------|--------|------------|\n| Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation | T1.1-T1.5 | Completed | 100% |\n| Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC | T2.1-T2.7 | Completed | 100% |\n| Phase 3: Deployment Integration | T3.1-T3.3 | Completed | 100% |\n| Phase 4: Permission Validation | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 5: Helm Validation | T5.1-T5.5 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation | T6.1-T6.3 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests | T7.1-T7.8 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 8: Security Audit | T8.1-T8.5 | Pending | 0% |\n\n**Total Progress: 30% Complete (15/50 tasks)**\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Design: `changes/AR-031/design.md`\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n- AR-030 Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md` (RBAC template patterns)\n- Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n- Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n- Helm Template Functions: https://helm.sh/docs/chart_template_guide/function_list/\n- agent-sandbox CRDs: https://sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml\">\nERROR [7:7] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [7:9] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [14:7] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [14:9] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [123:7] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [123:9] Missing , or : between flow map items\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics fil